verses.roman:
vāṇīnātha paṭṭanāyaka prasāda ānilā
kāśī-miśra aneka prasāda pāṭhāilā

synonyms: vāṇīnātha paṭṭanāyaka—Vāṇīnātha Paṭṭanāyaka; prasāda—prasāda; ānilā—brought in; kāśī-miśra—Kāśī Miśra; aneka prasāda—varieties of prasāda; pāṭhāilā—sent.
translation: Not only did Svarūpa Dāmodara Gosvāmī bring prasāda, but Vāṇīnātha Paṭṭanāyaka, as well as Kāśī Miśra, sent large quantities.
